Technology Brief -- Recognition Equipment Inc.:
   Letter of Intent Is Signed
   For $39 Million Acquisition
Recognition Equipment, which makes image and
data-processing equipment and software, said it would pay for
the assets primarily in cash. Closing of the transaction is
expected in March, the company said. It said the proposed
transaction is subject to completion of a definitive
agreement and board approval by both companies.
   Recognition Equipment stated the proposed acquisition
would give it the opportunity to "significantly expand" its
presence in automated work processing.